SIMPLE: cuticle
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cuticle
<hw>Cu"ti*cle</hw> <pr>(k⟦umac⟧"t⟦icr⟧*k'l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>cuticula</ets>, dim. of <ets>cutis</ets> skin; akin to E.
<ets>hide</ets> skin of an animal.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>The scarfskin or epidermis. See <er>Skin</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The outermost skin or pellicle of
a plant, found especially in leaves and young stems.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A thin skin formed on the surface of a
liquid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>cuticula</ent>⟦br⟧
